# üîí Auth Endpoints (API Key required)


Window command to set token:  set TOKEN=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...yourTokenHere


### ‚úÖ Register

```powershell
curl.exe -X POST http://localhost:5210/api/auth/register ^
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" ^
    -H "X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123" ^
    -d "{\"username\":\"testuser\", \"password\":\"Test@123\", \"role\":\"Admin\"}"
```

### ‚úÖ Login

```powershell
curl.exe -X POST http://localhost:5210/api/auth/login ^
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" ^
    -H "X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123" ^
    -d "{\"username\":\"testuser\", \"password\":\"Test@123\"}"
```

# üîí Inventory Endpoints (API Key + Bearer Token required)
_Replace `<TOKEN>` with your JWT token from login._

### ‚úÖ Get all inventory

```powershell
curl.exe -X GET http://localhost:5210/api/inventory ^
    -H "Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>" ^
    -H "X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123"
```

### ‚úÖ Create inventory item

```powershell
curl.exe -X POST http://localhost:5210/api/inventory ^
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" ^
    -H "Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>" ^
    -H "X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123" ^
    -d "{\"name\":\"Test Item\", \"quantity\":10, \"location\":\"Warehouse Z\"}"
```

# üîí Order Endpoints (API Key + Bearer Token required)

### ‚úÖ Get all orders (Admin only)

```powershell
curl.exe -X GET http://localhost:5210/api/order ^
    -H "Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>" ^
    -H "X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123"
```

### ‚úÖ Create order

```powershell
curl.exe -X POST http://localhost:5210/api/order ^
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" ^
    -H "Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>" ^
    -H "X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123" ^
    -d "{\"customerId\":1, \"datePlaced\":\"2025-06-28T00:00:00\"}"
```

# üîí Customer Endpoints (API Key + Bearer Token required)

### ‚úÖ Get all customers

```powershell
curl.exe -X GET http://localhost:5210/api/customer ^
    -H "Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>" ^
    -H "X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123"
```

### ‚úÖ Create customer

```powershell
curl.exe -X POST http://localhost:5210/api/customer ^
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" ^
    -H "Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>" ^
    -H "X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123" ^
    -d "{\"name\":\"John Doe\"}"
```
# üåê HTTP File Examples

Line to set token:  @token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...yourTokenHere


You can use the following `.http` file snippets with tools like [REST Client for VS Code](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=humao.rest-client) or [HTTPie](https://httpie.io/).

## üîí Auth Endpoints (API Key required)

### ‚úÖ Register

```http
POST http://localhost:5210/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123

{
    "username": "testuser",
    "password": "Test@123",
    "role": "Admin"
}
```

### ‚úÖ Login

```http
POST http://localhost:5210/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123

{
    "username": "testuser",
    "password": "Test@123"
}
```

## üîí Inventory Endpoints (API Key + Bearer Token required)
_Replace `{{TOKEN}}` with your JWT token from login._

### ‚úÖ Get all inventory

```http
GET http://localhost:5210/api/inventory
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}
X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123
```

### ‚úÖ Create inventory item

```http
POST http://localhost:5210/api/inventory
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}
X-API-KEY: supersecretkey123

{
    "name": "Test Item",
    "quantity": 10,
    "location": "Warehouse Z"
}
```

